Readings
RESULTS: 
1) there is a significant “book 
effect” on quiz scores →
compared to e-books, p-books 
appear to enable better 
reading comprehension
2) Regarding eye fatigue, students 
had significantly greater eye 
fatigue after reading e-books 
than after reading p-books. 
3) Students were satisfied with 
the e-book, but they preferred 
p-books.


